dct_description_sm: Stanford's Geographical Estabt. ; London : Longmans & Co. Paternoster Row.
Relief shown by hachures, spot heights, and coloring.
"Land below 1000 feet coloured green / land above 1000 feet coloured brown."
Shows boundaries, cities, waterways, low water (100 fathom line), roads.

Few additional details compared to 1889 map, along with presence of Kiel Canal ("North Sea & Baltic ship canal" on map) date this map to late 1890s. Denmark-German boundary predates Schleswig referendum in 1920.
